The 1911 replica of a Chained Bible - the version Oliver Cromwell ordered was shackled to pews - must be read with a magnifying glass. Fit in the psalm of your hand...the treasured discovery The 876-page tome was discovered at Leeds City Library when staff explored its stores during lockdowns. Rhian Isaac said how the bible came to them was "a mystery" but they had catalogued 3,000 new finds, many unusual, for people to see. Rhian added: "We would rather these books were used and read. That's what they were made for."